headline: Review & Preview: Who Needs AI?
summary: It turns out stocks can still rise without the vaunted artificial intelligence trade.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 664 points, or 1.4%, and the S&P 500 gained 0.9% despite down days from AI stalwarts Advanced Micro Devices (-4.2%), Nvidia (-2.6%), and Oracle (-1.6%).  Home builders Lennar and D.R. Horton were up 6.6% and 5.8%, respectively.

content.title: Review & Preview: Who Needs AI?
content.summary: It turns out stocks can still rise without the vaunted artificial intelligence trade.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 664 points, or 1.4%, and the S&P 500 gained 0.9% despite down days from AI stalwarts Advanced Micro Devices (-4.2%), Nvidia (-2.6%), and Oracle (-1.6%).  Home builders Lennar and D.R. Horton were up 6.6% and 5.8%, respectively.

headline: Alphabet Keeps Climbing, Nvidia Falls After Google-Meta Chip Talks
summary: Shares in Google parent Alphabet were rising premarket, while Nvidia fell, after it was reported that Google is in talks to supply chips to Meta Platforms.  Alphabet shares were up 1.5% at $328.36 in premarket trading.  The shares continued to hit new highs after news of talks for a potential deal with Meta for tensor processing units, which came at the expense of Nvidia shares, according to Scope Markets Analyst Joshua Mahony.

headline: ECB warns on stretched AI valuations and sovereign debt risks
